    "REASON: The proposed roof extension by reason of its inappropriate siting, detailed design, scale, massing, height, bulk and form is considered to form a dominant and discordant feature when seen from the public and private realms. It would cause harm to the character and appearance of the original building, the wider terrace setting as well as harming the significance of the setting of the adjacent Sotheby Road Conservation Area. The proposal is therefore contrary to the NPPF 2019, policies CS8 and CS9 of Islington's Core Strategy (2011), policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of Islington's Development Management Policies (2013) as well as the guidance of Islington's Urban Design Guide (2017)."
